# 1. いつか見た顔

Shizuku: Just ten more seconds. Keep going, everyone! You can do it!
First-Year Archery Club Member A: Hnng...! Fifty-five, fifty-six, fifty-seven...! Planking's so hard!
First-Year Archery Club Member B: My abs feel...like they're gonna...!
Shizuku: Sixty...! Okay, that's it.
First-Year Archery Club Member A: *Sigh* I thought I was done for!
Shizuku: Hehe. Nicely done.
Shizuku: Everyone, that was very impressive. You've all grown so much since you first joined this club, and this is proof of that.
Shizuku: I know it's not for a while, but I believe you'll all do wonderfully during our next tournament. So, please keep up the good work.
First-Year Archery Club Members A & B: *Gasp* Yes, Hinomori...!
Shizuku: Now that we're finished doing strength drills, let's get the targets ready...
First-Year Archery Club Member A: Oh, we'll put them up! Please take a break, Hinomori.
First-Year Archery Club Member A: This is so great! Hinomori praised us!
First-Year Archery Club Member B: And she seemed totally fine while planking just now! I guess idols need to keep their cool like that, huh?
Mafuyu: Hello, Hinomori.
Shizuku: Oh, Asahina, hello.
Mafuyu: Thank you for running strength drills with the first years today.
Mafuyu: I noticed that they were beginning to lose their focus a little after competing in the newcomer tournament, so I appreciate you stopping by today.
Shizuku: I didn't do anything special, really.
Shizuku: I mean, I haven't been able to show up for practice much lately because of MORE MORE JUMP! activities...
Mafuyu: Hehe. You're so modest, Hinomori.
First-Year Archery Club Member A: Hinomori! They're all set up!
Mafuyu: Ah, looks like you're needed.
Shizuku: Yes, I'll head over now. Good luck with practicing for the individuals match, Asahina!
Mafuyu: Thank you. I appreciate it.
Archery Club Members: Thank you very much! If you'll excuse us!
Mafuyu: Yes, good work today.
Mafuyu: Is that everyone...?
Shizuku: There was no one left in the changing room.
Mafuyu: Okay. Then, let's start closing up.
Shizuku: Oh, it's my turn today, so I'll return the key to the teachers.
Mafuyu: Thank you, but I'll go with you... There's something I need to ask them.
Shizuku: You will? Hehe. Then, shall we?
Shizuku: The first years have become much better archers since I last saw them.
Mafuyu: Yes, I believe the newcomer tournament played a big role.
Mafuyu: I suppose it's only natural to take official matches more seriously.
Shizuku: I see...
Shizuku: (When I was a first year, I received quite a lot of advice from others around this time of year, which helped me have more confidence in myself...)
Shizuku: (So much was going on back then...)
Mafuyu: Oh, it's the third years.
Shizuku: Huh?
Mafuyu: Look, they're all in the studying room together.
Shizuku: Oh, you're right. They all seem to be working very hard...
Mafuyu: They've all retired from club activities and have entrance exams coming up. And when I go down the third years' corridor, there's a sort of tension in the air.
Mafuyu: When we become third years, the time will also come for us to retire and study...
Shizuku: Yes, you're right... I know it's inevitable, but that time will eventually come...
Shizuku: I feel a little sad about that actually.
Mafuyu: Me too. Especially since we've been doing this since we were first years.
Shizuku: However, we have our futures to think about, and that's going to be our time to decide what we want to do in life...
Shizuku: Oh, Asahina, speaking of which... You're trying to get into medical school, yes?
Mafuyu: Huh? How did you know...?
Shizuku: Hehe. The first years told me. Some of them saw you buying study guides for it.
Mafuyu: I see. I feel a little embarrassed now.
Shizuku: No, don't. You'd make a wonderful doctor since you're such a kind person.
Shizuku: So, please do your best, Asahina.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu's Mother: Anyway, Mafuyu, do your best.
Mafuyu: Yes, you're right...
Mafuyu: I need to do my best.
Shizuku: What...?
Mafuyu: ...? Is something wrong, Hinomori?
Shizuku: Oh, um... It looked like you were thinking about something else just now.
Mafuyu: Hehe. I must've been thinking about entrance exams again and how much I have to study for them.
Shizuku: Oh, I see...
Shizuku: (But she seemed different compared to normal for some reason...)
Shizuku: (That expression she made...)
Shizuku: (I've seen it before somewhere...)
Shizuku: (Oh, it was that time...)
Mafuyu: That reminds me, Hinomori. When you were a first year, you decided to join the archery club as a way to improve your posture, yes?
Shizuku: Huh? Yes, that's right... I vaguely remember mentioning that when we first visited the club.
Mafuyu: Yes, and it left an impression on me because your posture was already very good. I suppose I should expect no less from an idol.
Shizuku: No, it's just... I was still trying to get started as an idol back then.
Shizuku: Also, Asahina, just now...
Teacher: Oh, what are you two still doing here? It's time to head home for the day.
Mafuyu: Oh, hello. We were just about to return the key to the archery range...
Teacher: Ah, I was just about to head back. Why don't I deliver that for you?
Mafuyu: You will? Thank you very much.
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: (That expression Asahina made...)
Shiho: Shizuku...
Shizuku: Eep!
Shiho: Huh?! I-Is everything okay?
Shizuku: Oh, Shii, it's you... I'm sorry. You startled me a little. Is there something you need...?
Shiho: You seemed more than a little startled. Well, anyway... I came to let you know that it's your turn to take a bath.
Shizuku: Oh, right... Thank you, Shii.
Shizuku: But there's something on my mind right now, so I think I'll wait until later to take a bath.
Shiho: ... Are you sure everything's okay?
Shizuku: Yes, but I appreciate your concern. Something is bothering me a little is all.
Shiho: Something's bothering you?
Shizuku: Yes, but I'm not sure how to put it into words...
Shizuku: So, I'd like some time to think on it more.
Shiho: To get a better idea... Okay, I understand.
Shiho: In that case, I'll let Mom know that she can go before you.
Shiho: Good luck, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Thank you, Shii! I really appreciate it!
Shizuku: (That expression Asahina made today...)
Shizuku: (It's just like what I saw that other time...)
Shizuku: (She seemed to have something on her mind that time as well.)
Shizuku: (Does that mean there's something bothering her...?)
Shizuku: But I could be jumping to the wrong conclusion...
Shizuku: What should I do...?
???: <...zuku!>
Shizuku: Hm? I thought I heard someone calling my...
KAITO: <Shizuku! Good evening!>
Miku: <Good evening! Sorry, we know it's late!>
Shizuku: KAITO? Miku? It's awfully late for you to be visiting me.
KAITO: <We came here hoping that we could ask you for some advice, Shizuku.>
Shizuku: Advice?
Miku: <Yes! We were thinking about altering some of our costumes for our next show.>
Miku: <They're ones that have been sitting in the dressing room and we want to change things up a little.>
Miku: <Remember how you all came up with your own costume designs? We decided to think up ideas for alterations in the same way...>
KAITO: <Unfortunately, this isn't exactly my forte.>
Miku: <Yes, me too. I've also been having trouble coming up with ideas.>
Miku: <So, Shizuku, since you're really good at coming up with design ideas, we thought we should ask you.>
Shizuku: Yes, I see... I'm not as good as you say I am, but I'll be more than happy to help.
KAITO: <Thank you, Shizuku!>
KAITO: <If possible, we'd like to have something warm that goes with the season...>
Shizuku: Something warm... In that case, why not try using a fluffy material that insulates well for the sleeves?
Shizuku: Also, something that looks like ice crystals. Not only will they look pretty, they'll give your costumes a nice, wintery feel.
KAITO: <Yes...! Those sound perfect!>
Shizuku: You could even have imitation snow fall from above to go along with your costumes.
Shizuku: (Oh... Snow...)
Miku: <Shizuku...?>
Shizuku: I-I'm sorry! Our conversation reminded me of something else...
KAITO: <Something else? Oh, is there something bothering you...?>
Shizuku: Well, um...
Shizuku: It has a bit to do with something I remembered about my friend from club...
Shizuku: But it's more of a personal matter...
KAITO: <If talking to someone else about it will make you feel better, I'll be more than happy to listen.>
Shizuku: KAITO... Hehe. Thank you very much.
Shizuku: Then, if you don't mind...
